 :tx/rationale "DAEMON-ARCH-1: MCP Protocol Reuse Architecture. The daemon reuses the EXACT JSON-RPC protocol and tool dispatch from mcp.rs (1,731 LOC). The call_tool() function (mcp.rs:319-344) dispatches to 11 tool handlers. These handlers must be made pub(crate) so daemon.rs can call them. The daemon IS the MCP server with a different transport layer (Unix socket at .braid/daemon.sock instead of stdin/stdout). This means daemon.rs contains ONLY: (1) lifecycle management (start/stop/lock/signal), (2) socket accept loop, (3) runtime datom emission wrapper, (4) connection management. All tool logic stays in mcp.rs. The handle_tools_call function (mcp.rs:1131-1156) with its guidance footer injection (append_guidance_footer, mcp.rs:1167-1201) is shared between MCP stdio mode and daemon socket mode. Verification: after extraction, existing MCP tests (expected_tool_count, tool_names_match_expected_set, tool_descriptions_quality) must continue to pass unchanged. ADR-DAEMON-002."
